title: Gameover Zeus
extract: Gameover Zeus is a peer-to-peer (P2P) malware extension of the Zeus family that steals bank credentials and is a distributor for CryptoLocker ransomware. It was first discovered in 2011. Cyber criminals use it to "filter" money away from banking customers.
